<subSubSection id="C37B9DF9FFBFFF978FC44E8EFDA9A6F0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDECE72FFBFFF978FC44E8EFEF6A58A" blockId="19.[189,310,437,463]" box="[189,310,437,463]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<heading id="D096791EFFBFFF978FC44E8EFEF6A58A" bold="true" box="[189,310,437,463]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFBFFF978FC44E8EFEF6A58A" bold="true" box="[189,310,437,463]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDECE72FFBFFF978FC44EDFFDA9A6F0" blockId="19.[189,1399,484,693]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Male abdominal tergites T5 with a contiguous diffuse dark brown stripe, T6 light with a very faint dark stripe (
<figureCitation id="135AD2F7FFBFFF978E684D32FEB1A666" box="[273,369,521,547]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[215,1384,1143,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1398,1108,1904]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. Adult habitus. A–B. D. vulcana Graber, 1957 (MNHN). A. ♂. B. ♀. C–D. D. mylenae David &amp; Yassin sp. nov. (MNHN). C. ♂. D. ♀. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251585/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
); hypandrium narrow with an elongated anterior phragma; outer paraphyses posterior margin curved; aedeagus pilosity tapering at tip (
<figureCitation id="135AD2F7FFBFFF978D834D16FCBAA60D" box="[762,890,557,584]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[225,1374,307,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[189,1398,265,1858]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 9. Terminalia of the ‘D. vulcana species complex’. A, C, E. D. vulcana Graber, 1957 (MNHN). A, C. ♂. E. ♀. B, D, F. D. mylenae David &amp; Yassin sp. nov. (MNHN). B, D. ♂. F. ♀. Scale bars: A–B = 50 µm; D–F = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251587/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9A, C</figureCitation>
); female abdominal tergites T2–T4 without a diffuse pale region on the antero-distal margins, T5 with diffusely dark stripe (
<figureCitation id="135AD2F7FFBFFF978B2E4D69FB72A629" box="[1111,1202,594,620]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[215,1384,1143,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1398,1108,1904]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. Adult habitus. A–B. D. vulcana Graber, 1957 (MNHN). A. ♂. B. ♀. C–D. D. mylenae David &amp; Yassin sp. nov. (MNHN). C. ♂. D. ♀. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251585/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
); oviscapt fourth posterior peg-like outer ovisensillum on the same axis with the third and fifth ovisensilla, with anterior ovisensilla short and thick (
<figureCitation id="135AD2F7FFBFFF978D794DA0FD9CA6F0" box="[512,604,667,693]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[225,1374,307,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[189,1398,265,1858]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 9. Terminalia of the ‘D. vulcana species complex’. A, C, E. D. vulcana Graber, 1957 (MNHN). A, C. ♂. E. ♀. B, D, F. D. mylenae David &amp; Yassin sp. nov. (MNHN). B, D. ♂. F. ♀. Scale bars: A–B = 50 µm; D–F = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251587/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
