<collectingCountry id="F3768EE2FFBFFF978C774B00FCB7A010" box="[782,887,1083,1109]" name="Tanzania" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3768EE2FFBFFF978CC84B00FBF2A010" box="[945,1074,1083,1109]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37B9DF9FFBFFF908FC44B45FD4FA50E" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDECE72FFBFFF978FC44B45FEEFA0DD" blockId="19.[189,303,1150,1176]" box="[189,303,1150,1176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<heading id="D096791EFFBFFF978FC44B45FEEFA0DD" bold="true" box="[189,303,1150,1176]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFBFFF978FC44B45FEEFA0DD" bold="true" box="[189,303,1150,1176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDECE72FFBFFF908FC44B95FD4FA50E" blockId="19.[189,1399,1198,2027]" lastBlockId="20.[189,1398,267,332]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
The type material of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978EB44B95FDBBA08C" author="Graber H." box="[461,635,1198,1225]" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Jahrbucher" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="305 - 316" part="85" refId="ref12401" refString="Graber H. 1957. Afrikanische Drosophiliden als Blutenbesucher. Zoologische Jahrbucher 85: 305 - 316." title="Afrikanische Drosophiliden als Blutenbesucher" type="journal article" year="1957">Graber (1957)</bibRefCitation>
consisted of six males and six females from 
<collectingRegion id="49A50090FFBFFF978BBC4B95FAB6A08D" box="[1221,1398,1198,1224]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Sud-Kivu" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Kivu Province</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="F3768EE2FFBFFF978FBC4BE9FDABA0A8" box="[197,619,1234,1261]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Democratic Republic of the Congo</collectingCountry>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978D064BE8FC20A0A8" author="Tsacas L. &amp; Chassagnard M. - T." box="[639,992,1234,1261]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="427 - 432" part="96" refId="ref13191" refString="Tsacas L. &amp; Chassagnard M. - T. 1992. L'identite de Drosophila (Sophophora) vulcana Graber (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France 96: 427 - 432." title="L'identite de Drosophila (Sophophora) vulcana Graber (Diptera, Drosophilidae)" type="journal article" year="1992">Tsacas &amp; Chassagnard (1992)</bibRefCitation>
examined this material and found five males and six females (probably the male used by Graber for dissection and genitalia illustration was lost). Of the five remaining males, only one belonged to a ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFBFFF978C1F4A27FC30A170" authorityName="Meijere" authorityYear="1916" box="[870,1008,1308,1333]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montium">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFBFFF978C1F4A27FC30A170" box="[870,1008,1308,1333]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. montium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group’ that 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978BAD4A27FAB6A173" author="Tsacas L." box="[1236,1398,1308,1334]" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe entomologique de France" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="419 - 438" part="20" refId="ref13148" refString="Tsacas L. 1984. Nouvelles donnees sur la biogeographie et l'evolution du groupe Drosophila melanogaster en Afrique. Description de six nouvelles especes (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Annales de la Societe entomologique de France 20: 419 - 438." title="Nouvelles donnees sur la biogeographie et l'evolution du groupe Drosophila melanogaster en Afrique. Description de six nouvelles especes (Diptera, Drosophilidae)" type="journal article" year="1984">Tsacas (1984)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFBFFF978E3A4A7AFE6EA11F" authorityName="Tsacas" authorityYear="1984" box="[323,430,1344,1370]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ifestia">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFBFFF978E3A4A7AFE6EA11F" box="[323,430,1344,1370]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. ifestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Of the six females, five belonged to the ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFBFFF978CE14A7AFBE2A11F" authorityName="Meijere" authorityYear="1916" box="[920,1058,1345,1370]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montium">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFBFFF978CE14A7AFBE2A11F" box="[920,1058,1345,1370]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. montium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group’. Two females sojourned in alcohol and lost coloration, whereas the remaining three females were pinned and had dark wings, pleurae and legs in agreement with the original description of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978B754AB2FB79A1E1" author="Graber H." box="[1036,1209,1417,1444]" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Jahrbucher" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="305 - 316" part="85" refId="ref12401" refString="Graber H. 1957. Afrikanische Drosophiliden als Blutenbesucher. Zoologische Jahrbucher 85: 305 - 316." title="Afrikanische Drosophiliden als Blutenbesucher" type="journal article" year="1957">Graber (1957)</bibRefCitation>
. For abdominal coloration, this description indicates “uniform schwarzbraune glänzende Tergite” (uniform black-brown shining tergite). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978E074AE9FD5AA1A9" author="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R." box="[382,666,1490,1516]" journalOrPublisher="The University of Texas Publication" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 102" part="7213" refId="ref12038" refString="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R. 1972. The Drosophila melanogaster species group. The University of Texas Publication 7213: 1 - 102." title="The Drosophila melanogaster species group" type="journal article" year="1972">Bock &amp; Wheeler (1972)</bibRefCitation>
described a strain from Mount Selinda (
<collectingCountry id="F3768EE2FFBFFF978B0C4AE9FB36A1A8" box="[1141,1270,1490,1517]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
) attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFBFFF978FA24ACCFE9BA255" authorityName="Graber" authorityYear="1957" box="[219,347,1526,1552]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcana">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFBFFF978FA24ACCFE9BA255" box="[219,347,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. vulcana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by S. Paterson. They showed, however, the presence of two types of male genitalia in this strain. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978E764920FDB5A270" author="Tsacas L. &amp; Chassagnard M. - T." box="[271,629,1563,1589]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="427 - 432" part="96" refId="ref13191" refString="Tsacas L. &amp; Chassagnard M. - T. 1992. L'identite de Drosophila (Sophophora) vulcana Graber (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France 96: 427 - 432." title="L'identite de Drosophila (Sophophora) vulcana Graber (Diptera, Drosophilidae)" type="journal article" year="1992">Tsacas &amp; Chassagnard (1992)</bibRefCitation>
reanalyzed this strain and found that only one of the two types existed at the time of their examination. They concluded that the original strain consisted of two distinct species with one having subsequently gone extinct. They also suggested that male genitalia of the type of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978FA749B3FEBFA2E7" author="Seguy E." box="[222,383,1672,1698]" journalOrPublisher="Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="319 - 380" part="8" refId="ref12988" refString="Seguy E. 1938. Mission scientifique de l'Omo. Diptera. I. Nematocera et Brachycera. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris 8: 319 - 380." title="Mission scientifique de l'Omo. Diptera. I. Nematocera et Brachycera" type="journal article" year="1938">Séguy (1938)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFBFFF978ECB49B2FDE2A2E7" box="[434,546,1673,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFBFFF978ECB49B2FDE2A2E7" box="[434,546,1673,1698]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
corresponded to the genitalia of the surviving species in this strain. We dissected males from the strain of Mount Selinda and found that the illustration of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978B094996FECBA2AE" author="Tsacas L. &amp; Chassagnard M. - T." journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="427 - 432" part="96" refId="ref13191" refString="Tsacas L. &amp; Chassagnard M. - T. 1992. L'identite de Drosophila (Sophophora) vulcana Graber (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France 96: 427 - 432." title="L'identite de Drosophila (Sophophora) vulcana Graber (Diptera, Drosophilidae)" type="journal article" year="1992">Tsacas &amp; Chassagnard (1992)</bibRefCitation>
of the 
<typeStatus id="54DA70D0FFBFFF978E2349EAFE01A2AE" box="[346,449,1745,1771]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFBFFF978E9C49E9FD93A2AE" box="[485,595,1746,1771]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFBFFF978E9C49E9FD93A2AE" box="[485,595,1746,1771]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the partial fusion of the cercal ventral lobe (secondary clasper), characteristic of the strain of Mount Selinda. Moreover, the pale male abdominal pigmentation of the strain of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978E534821FD8CA371" author="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R." box="[298,588,1818,1844]" journalOrPublisher="The University of Texas Publication" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 102" part="7213" refId="ref12038" refString="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R. 1972. The Drosophila melanogaster species group. The University of Texas Publication 7213: 1 - 102." title="The Drosophila melanogaster species group" type="journal article" year="1972">Bock &amp; Wheeler (1972)</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation id="135AD2F7FFBFFF978D264821FD7DA371" box="[607,701,1818,1844]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1889,1915]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,292,1806]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[228,1359,267,1833]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Adult habitus. A–B. D. seguyi Smart, 1945 (MNHN). A. ♂. B. ♀. C–D. D. malagassya Tsacas &amp; Rafael, 1982 (MNHN). C. ♂. D. ♀. E–F. D. curta Chassagnard &amp; Tsacas, 1997 (MNHN). E. ♂. F. ♀. G–H. D. chocolata Yassin &amp; David sp. nov. (MNHN). G. ♂. H. ♀. Only dark morphs of females of species with female-limited color dimorphism are shown. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251577/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
) clearly contrasts with the description of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978BCA4821FA95A371" author="Seguy E." box="[1203,1365,1818,1844]" journalOrPublisher="Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="319 - 380" part="8" refId="ref12988" refString="Seguy E. 1938. Mission scientifique de l'Omo. Diptera. I. Nematocera et Brachycera. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris 8: 319 - 380." title="Mission scientifique de l'Omo. Diptera. I. Nematocera et Brachycera" type="journal article" year="1938">Séguy (1938)</bibRefCitation>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFBFFF978FC4487BFEEFA31C" box="[189,303,1856,1881]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFBFFF978FC4487BFEEFA31C" box="[189,303,1856,1881]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: “tergites largement bordés de brun noir, dernier segment d’un noir luisant” [tergites with large brownish black stripe, last segment shiny black]. On the contrary, abdominal pigmentation of the strain of Mount Selinda corresponded to the abovementioned original description of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978BBC48B3FAB3A3E6" author="Graber H." box="[1221,1395,1928,1955]" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Jahrbucher" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="305 - 316" part="85" refId="ref12401" refString="Graber H. 1957. Afrikanische Drosophiliden als Blutenbesucher. Zoologische Jahrbucher 85: 305 - 316." title="Afrikanische Drosophiliden als Blutenbesucher" type="journal article" year="1957">Graber (1957)</bibRefCitation>
. Therefore, we concur with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978D754897FCF4A383" author="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R." box="[524,820,1964,1990]" journalOrPublisher="The University of Texas Publication" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 102" part="7213" refId="ref12038" refString="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R. 1972. The Drosophila melanogaster species group. The University of Texas Publication 7213: 1 - 102." title="The Drosophila melanogaster species group" type="journal article" year="1972">Bock &amp; Wheeler (1972)</bibRefCitation>
for considering the strain of Mount Selinda to belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFBFFF978E4848E9FE72A3AE" authorityName="Graber" authorityYear="1957" box="[305,434,2001,2027]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcana">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFBFFF978E4848E9FE72A3AE" box="[305,434,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. vulcana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978EB948EAFD63A3AE" author="Okada T. &amp; Asada N. &amp; Kawanaka K." box="[448,675,2001,2027]" journalOrPublisher="African Study Monographs" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="159 - 163" part="8" refId="ref12771" refString="Okada T., Asada N. &amp; Kawanaka K. 1988. A result of drosophilid survey in Tanzania. African Study Monographs 8: 159 - 163." title="A result of drosophilid survey in Tanzania" type="journal article" year="1988">
Okada 
<emphasis id="B9151260FFBFFF978D6A48E9FD8EA3AE" box="[531,590,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
(1988)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from 
<collectingCountry id="F3768EE2FFBFFF978C9A48EAFB90A3AE" box="[995,1104,2001,2027]" name="Tanzania" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFBFFF978BF548EAFAB6A3AE" author="Takada H. &amp; Woodruff R. C. &amp; Thompson J. N." box="[1164,1398,2001,2027]" journalOrPublisher="Entomological News" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="246 - 255" part="101" refId="ref13020" refString="Takada H., Woodruff R. C. &amp; Thompson J. N. 1990. Collections of Drosophilidae (Diptera) in Kenya, with description of a new species of Dettopsomyia. Entomological News 101: 246 - 255." title="Collections of Drosophilidae (Diptera) in Kenya, with description of a new species of Dettopsomyia" type="journal article" year="1990">
Takada 
<emphasis id="B9151260FFBFFF978B9E48E9FAE1A3AE" box="[1255,1313,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
(1990)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated its presence in 
<collectingCountry id="F3768EE2FFB8FF908E9C4E37FDF5A563" box="[485,565,268,294]" name="Kenya" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Kenya</collectingCountry>
, suggesting its widespread distribution in East Africa. Females do not exhibit a sex-limited color dimorphism.
</paragraph>
